As an independent entrepreneur who is introverted and prioritizes privacy, running a business should not feel this awkward all the time, but it often does. Most online resources and mentors tell you to interact with large (evil) tech companies in an extroverted way. Here, I am advertising to follow the algorithm and share your personal charm. On that service, get verified, stay online 24/7, answer questions with your own video, and respond immediately. Video, video, video.
1/3
This is a year of transformation for me.
I don't want to invest my money, data, and energy in large tech companies anymore, nor do I want to listen to mentors who only offer one-size-fits-all extroverted solutions. I am exploring new business models and trying to overcome my long-held idea that success can only be achieved by following a specific way.
Wish me luck!
First step has been taken.
I have quit FB, removed all Meta and Pinterest trackers from my website, and logged out of my personal WhatsApp account.
Yesterday, I also removed the last external tracker from my website - Google Analytics, feels great.
In order to better support GDPR, I recently subscribed to a European CRM service, and will be migrating my business there in the coming weeks.
I have transferred MX records to Proton, now have full SPF, DKIM, and DMARC without having to pay Google for basic email verification.
3/3
